   "source": [
    "# E-Commerce Sales Analysis\n",
    "\n",
    "**End-to-end analysis of e-commerce sales data using Python, Pandas, and Matplotlib.**\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "### Objectives\n",
    "1. Load and profile the dataset\n",
    "2. Clean and validate data quality\n",
    "3. Analyze total revenue and key metrics\n",
    "4. Rank top products by revenue\n",
    "5. Break down sales by region\n",
    "6. Analyze sales trends over time\n",
    "7. Category-level performance\n",
    "8. Quantity vs Revenue analysis\n",
    "9. Key business insights\n",
    "\n",
    "**Dataset:** `ecommerce_sample_dataset.csv`  \n",
    "**Columns:** OrderID, Product, Category, Sales, Quantity, OrderDate, Region"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["## Step 1: Import Libraries"]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import matplotlib.ticker as mticker\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "import warnings\n",
    "warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plot styling\n",
    "plt.rcParams['figure.figsize'] = (10, 5)\n",
    "plt.rcParams['axes.spines.top'] = False\n",
    "plt.rcParams['axes.spines.right'] = False\n",
    "sns.set_palette('Set2')\n",
    "\n",
    "print('Libraries loaded successfully.')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["## Step 2: Load the Dataset"]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "df = pd.read_csv('ecommerce_sample_dataset.csv')\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f'Dataset shape: {df.shape[0]} rows x {df.shape[1]} columns')\n",
    "print(f'Columns: {list(df.columns)}')\n",
    "df.head(10)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["## Step 3: Data Quality Check"]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Data types\n",
    "print('=== Data Types ===')\n",
    "print(df.dtypes)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Missing values\n",
    "print('\\n=== Missing Values ===')\n",
    "missing = df.isnull().sum()\n",
    "print(missing)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Duplicates\n",
    "print(f'\\nDuplicate rows: {df.duplicated().sum()}')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Negative sales check\n",
    "neg_sales = df[df['Sales'] < 0]\n",
    "print(f'Negative Sales values: {len(neg_sales)}')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Convert OrderDate\n",
    "df['OrderDate'] = pd.to_datetime(df['OrderDate'])\n",
    "print(f'\\nDate range: {df[\"OrderDate\"].min()} to {df[\"OrderDate\"].max()}')\n",
    "print('\\nData quality check passed!')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["## Step 4: Descriptive Statistics & Key Metrics"]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "print('=== KEY BUSINESS METRICS ===')\n",
    "total_revenue   = df['Sales'].sum()\n",
    "total_orders    = df['OrderID'].nunique()\n",
    "total_quantity  = df['Quantity'].sum()\n",
    "avg_order_value = df['Sales'].mean()\n",
    "num_products    = df['Product'].nunique()\n",
    "num_categories  = df['Category'].nunique()\n",
    "num_regions     = df['Region'].nunique()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f'Total Revenue      : ${total_revenue:,.2f}')\n",
    "print(f'Total Orders       : {total_orders}')\n",
    "print(f'Total Units Sold   : {total_quantity}')\n",
    "print(f'Avg Order Value    : ${avg_order_value:,.2f}')\n",
    "print(f'Unique Products    : {num_products}')\n",
    "print(f'Categories         : {num_categories}')\n",
    "print(f'Regions Covered    : {num_regions}')\n",
    "\n",
    "print('\\n=== SALES STATISTICS ===')\n",
    "print(df[['Sales', 'Quantity']].describe().round(2))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["## Step 5: Top Products by Revenue"]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "top_products = (\n",
    "    df.groupby('Product')\n",
    "      .agg(Total_Revenue=('Sales','sum'), Orders=('OrderID','count'), Units=('Quantity','sum'))\n",
    "      .sort_values('Total_Revenue', ascending=False)\n",
    "      .reset_index()\n",
    ")\n",
    "top_products['Revenue_Share_%'] = (top_products['Total_Revenue'] / top_products['Total_Revenue'].sum() * 100).round(1)\n",
    "\n",
    "print('=== TOP PRODUCTS BY REVENUE ===')\n",
    "print(top_products.to_string(index=False))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Bar chart\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 5))\n",
    "bars = ax.barh(top_products['Product'], top_products['Total_Revenue'], color=sns.color_palette('Set2', len(top_products)))\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel('Total Revenue ($)')\n",
    "ax.set_title('Top Products by Total Revenue', fontsize=14, fontweight='bold')\n",
    "ax.xaxis.set_major_formatter(mticker.FuncFormatter(lambda x, _: f'${x:,.0f}'))\n",
    "for bar, val in zip(bars, top_products['Total_Revenue']):\n",
    "    ax.text(bar.get_width() + 5, bar.get_y() + bar.get_height()/2, f'${val:,.0f}', va='center', fontsize=9)\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["## Step 6: Sales by Region"]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "region_summary = (\n",
    "    df.groupby('Region')\n",
    "      .agg(Total_Revenue=('Sales','sum'), Orders=('OrderID','count'), Avg_Order=('Sales','mean'))\n",
    "      .sort_values('Total_Revenue', ascending=False)\n",
    "      .reset_index()\n",
    ")\n",
    "region_summary['Revenue_Share_%'] = (region_summary['Total_Revenue'] / region_summary['Total_Revenue'].sum() * 100).round(1)\n",
    "region_summary['Avg_Order'] = region_summary['Avg_Order'].round(2)\n",
    "\n",
    "print('=== SALES BY REGION ===')\n",
    "print(region_summary.to_string(index=False))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Pie + bar side by side\n",
    "fig, (ax1, ax2) = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(13, 5))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Pie chart\n",
    "ax1.pie(region_summary['Total_Revenue'], labels=region_summary['Region'],\n",
    "        autopct='%1.1f%%', startangle=90, colors=sns.color_palette('Set2'))\n",
    "ax1.set_title('Revenue Share by Region', fontsize=13, fontweight='bold')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Bar chart\n",
    "ax2.bar(region_summary['Region'], region_summary['Total_Revenue'], color=sns.color_palette('Set2'))\n",
    "ax2.set_xlabel('Region')\n",
    "ax2.set_ylabel('Total Revenue ($)')\n",
    "ax2.set_title('Total Revenue by Region', fontsize=13, fontweight='bold')\n",
    "ax2.yaxis.set_major_formatter(mticker.FuncFormatter(lambda x, _: f'${x:,.0f}'))\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["## Step 7: Sales Trend Over Time"]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "daily_sales = df.groupby('OrderDate')['Sales'].sum().reset_index().sort_values('OrderDate')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Add 7-day rolling average\n",
    "daily_sales['Rolling_7d'] = daily_sales['Sales'].rolling(window=7, min_periods=1).mean()\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 5))\n",
    "ax.plot(daily_sales['OrderDate'], daily_sales['Sales'], color='#4C72B0', alpha=0.4, linewidth=1, label='Daily Sales')\n",
    "ax.plot(daily_sales['OrderDate'], daily_sales['Rolling_7d'], color='#DD8452', linewidth=2.5, label='7-Day Rolling Avg')\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel('Date')\n",
    "ax.set_ylabel('Sales ($)')\n",
    "ax.set_title('Daily Sales Trend with 7-Day Rolling Average', fontsize=14, fontweight='bold')\n",
    "ax.yaxis.set_major_formatter(mticker.FuncFormatter(lambda x, _: f'${x:,.0f}'))\n",
    "ax.legend()\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f'Peak single-day revenue: ${daily_sales[\"Sales\"].max():,.2f} on {daily_sales.loc[daily_sales[\"Sales\"].idxmax(), \"OrderDate\"].date()}')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["## Step 8: Category-Level Performance"]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "cat_summary = (\n",
    "    df.groupby('Category')\n",
    "      .agg(\n",
    "          Total_Revenue=('Sales','sum'),\n",
    "          Orders=('OrderID','count'),\n",
    "          Units_Sold=('Quantity','sum'),\n",
    "          Avg_Sale=('Sales','mean'),\n",
    "          Max_Sale=('Sales','max')\n",
    "      )\n",
    "      .sort_values('Total_Revenue', ascending=False)\n",
    "      .reset_index()\n",
    ")\n",
    "cat_summary['Avg_Sale'] = cat_summary['Avg_Sale'].round(2)\n",
    "cat_summary['Revenue_%'] = (cat_summary['Total_Revenue'] / cat_summary['Total_Revenue'].sum() * 100).round(1)\n",
    "\n",
    "print('=== CATEGORY PERFORMANCE ===')\n",
    "print(cat_summary.to_string(index=False))\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(13, 5))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Revenue by category\n",
    "axes[0].bar(cat_summary['Category'], cat_summary['Total_Revenue'], color=sns.color_palette('Set2'))\n",
    "axes[0].set_title('Revenue by Category', fontsize=13, fontweight='bold')\n",
    "axes[0].set_ylabel('Total Revenue ($)')\n",
    "axes[0].yaxis.set_major_formatter(mticker.FuncFormatter(lambda x, _: f'${x:,.0f}'))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Units sold by category\n",
    "axes[1].bar(cat_summary['Category'], cat_summary['Units_Sold'], color=sns.color_palette('husl', len(cat_summary)))\n",
    "axes[1].set_title('Units Sold by Category', fontsize=13, fontweight='bold')\n",
    "axes[1].set_ylabel('Total Units')\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["## Step 9: Quantity vs Revenue — Scatter Analysis"]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "product_agg = (\n",
    "    df.groupby(['Product', 'Category'])\n",
    "      .agg(Total_Revenue=('Sales','sum'), Total_Quantity=('Quantity','sum'))\n",
    "      .reset_index()\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))\n",
    "categories = product_agg['Category'].unique()\n",
    "palette = sns.color_palette('Set2', len(categories))\n",
    "for cat, color in zip(categories, palette):\n",
    "    subset = product_agg[product_agg['Category'] == cat]\n",
    "    ax.scatter(subset['Total_Quantity'], subset['Total_Revenue'], label=cat, s=120, color=color)\n",
    "    for _, row in subset.iterrows():\n",
    "        ax.annotate(row['Product'], (row['Total_Quantity'], row['Total_Revenue']),\n",
    "                    textcoords='offset points', xytext=(5, 5), fontsize=8)\n",
    "\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel('Total Quantity Sold')\n",
    "ax.set_ylabel('Total Revenue ($)')\n",
    "ax.set_title('Revenue vs Quantity by Product', fontsize=14, fontweight='bold')\n",
    "ax.yaxis.set_major_formatter(mticker.FuncFormatter(lambda x, _: f'${x:,.0f}'))\n",
    "ax.legend(title='Category')\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["## Step 10: Key Insights & Business Recommendations"]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Auto-generate insights from data\n",
    "top_product   = top_products.iloc[0]\n",
    "top_region    = region_summary.iloc[0]\n",
    "top_category  = cat_summary.iloc[0]\n",
    "low_category  = cat_summary.iloc[-1]\n",
    "\n",
    "print('=' * 55)\n",
    "print('          KEY INSIGHTS & RECOMMENDATIONS')\n",
    "print('=' * 55)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f'''\n",
    "REVENUE OVERVIEW\n",
    "  Total Revenue   : ${df[\"Sales\"].sum():,.2f}\n",
    "  Total Orders    : {df[\"OrderID\"].nunique()}\n",
    "  Avg Order Value : ${df[\"Sales\"].mean():,.2f}\n",
    "\n",
    "TOP PERFORMER\n",
    "  Best Product  : {top_product[\"Product\"]} (${top_product[\"Total_Revenue\"]:,.2f}, {top_product[\"Revenue_Share_%\"]}% of revenue)\n",
    "  Best Region   : {top_region[\"Region\"]} (${top_region[\"Total_Revenue\"]:,.2f}, {top_region[\"Revenue_Share_%\"]}% share)\n",
    "  Best Category : {top_category[\"Category\"]} (${top_category[\"Total_Revenue\"]:,.2f})\n",
    "\n",
    "OPPORTUNITIES\n",
    "  Lowest Category : {low_category[\"Category\"]} — potential for targeted promotions\n",
    "  Focus Region    : Lowest revenue region needs demand gen or pricing review\n",
    "\n",
    "RECOMMENDATIONS\n",
    "  1. Double down on {top_category[\"Category\"]} — highest revenue, expand SKUs\n",
    "  2. Investigate {low_category[\"Category\"]} underperformance — pricing or demand?\n",
    "  3. Prioritize {top_region[\"Region\"]} for inventory placement (top market)\n",
    "  4. Cross-sell high-quantity/low-revenue products with high-margin items\n",
    "  5. Use rolling 7-day trend to detect seasonal spikes for inventory planning\n",
    "''')"
   ]
  }
